<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="283" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,825,2040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,969,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sittichaya &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2020" box="[333,487,970,996]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Eggersanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[333,487,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Eggersanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" box="[708,853,970,996]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Arixyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[708,853,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Arixyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[870,968,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1719,1744]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,190,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[159,1428,181,1693]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Morphological appearance of Eggersanthus sublaevis (Eggers, 1927) (A,B,C,G,H,I), Arixyleborus rugosipes Hopkins, 1915 (type species of Arixyleborus) (D,E,F,J,K,L)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833599" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833599/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Figure 2</figureCitation>
and Table 1) and can be separated from other xyleborine genera by the following combination of characters: pronotum in dorsal view rectangular (
<typeStatus box="[1339,1389,1006,1032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
a in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Dole, S. A. &amp; Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[151,347,1042,1068]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" pagination="568 - 584" refId="ref3545" refString="Hulcr, J., Dole, S. A., Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2007) Cladistic review of generic taxonomic characters in Xyleborina (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 568 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00386. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Hulcr 
<emphasis box="[223,273,1042,1068]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), anterior margin weakly concave, without a median row of serrations, corners sharply quadrate, anterolateral corners asperate with 4–5 serrations forming a 90° angle; pronotum in lateral view with disc longer than anterior slope (
<typeStatus box="[371,421,1114,1140]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[427,470,1114,1140]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Dole, S. A. &amp; Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[475,667,1114,1140]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" pagination="568 - 584" refId="ref3545" refString="Hulcr, J., Dole, S. A., Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2007) Cladistic review of generic taxonomic characters in Xyleborina (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 568 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00386. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Hulcr 
<emphasis box="[545,593,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
); antennal funicle 4-segmented, club obliquely truncate 
<typeStatus box="[1289,1337,1114,1140]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
2 (
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Dole, S. A. &amp; Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I." pageId="1" pageNumber="283" pagination="568 - 584" refId="ref3545" refString="Hulcr, J., Dole, S. A., Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2007) Cladistic review of generic taxonomic characters in Xyleborina (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 568 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00386. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Hulcr 
<emphasis box="[151,207,1150,1176]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), approximately circular, as long as wide, segment 1 corneous, nearly encircling anterior face, segment 2 pubescent, visible on anterior face only; elytral declivity with granulate striae and interstriae; protibiae very slender, distinctly triangular, posterior face flat and unarmed; scutellum large, triangular, clearly visible from dorsal view; elytra attenuate; and no mycangial tufts present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,825,2040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1293,1320]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Description:</emphasis>
Female. Length 
<quantity box="[533,681,1293,1320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.125" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.05" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" unit="mm" value="2.125" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="2.05">2.05–2.2 mm</quantity>
and 2.73–2.90 times as long as wide (n = 4). Body color light brown to brown, darker in appearance on pronotum anterior slope and elytral declivity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,825,2040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,1366,1392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Head.</emphasis>
Mandibular base broad, mandibles short. Epistoma with long yellowish setae arranged in a single row. Frons flat, shagreened, with an indistinct small flat median line; vestiture of fine hairs of variable length. Eye comparatively large, shallowly emarginate at antennal insertion, lower portion distinctly larger than upper. Submentum shallowly impressed, shaped as a very narrow triangle. Antennal scape short and thick; pedicel cup-shaped, longer than funicle; funicle 4-segmented, antennal club 
<typeStatus box="[691,739,1510,1536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
2 (
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Dole, S. A. &amp; Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[773,965,1510,1536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" pagination="568 - 584" refId="ref3545" refString="Hulcr, J., Dole, S. A., Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2007) Cladistic review of generic taxonomic characters in Xyleborina (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 568 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00386. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Hulcr 
<emphasis box="[844,892,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), moderate in size, approximately circular, as long as wide, segment 1 prominent, distinctly corneous, its margin convex, costate, nearly covering posterior face; second segment not sclerotized, soft, visible on anterior face only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,825,2040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1618,1644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Pronotum.</emphasis>
Robust, in dorsal view rectangular (
<typeStatus box="[740,790,1618,1644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
a in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Dole, S. A. &amp; Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[849,1046,1618,1644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" pagination="568 - 584" refId="ref3545" refString="Hulcr, J., Dole, S. A., Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2007) Cladistic review of generic taxonomic characters in Xyleborina (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 568 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00386. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Hulcr 
<emphasis box="[921,971,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), anterior margin weakly concave, without a median row of serrations, corners sharply quadrate, anterolateral corners asperate with 4–5 serrations forming a 90° angle, asperities on anterior slope short, moderately sized and coarse; disc shagreened; basal margin bisinuate; no mycangial tuft; pronotum in lateral view with disc longer than anterior slope (
<typeStatus box="[1197,1247,1726,1752]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[1255,1299,1726,1752]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Dole, S. A. &amp; Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I." pageId="1" pageNumber="283" pagination="568 - 584" refId="ref3545" refString="Hulcr, J., Dole, S. A., Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2007) Cladistic review of generic taxonomic characters in Xyleborina (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 568 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00386. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Hulcr 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,825,2040]" box="[199,1414,1797,1824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1797,1824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Scutellum.</emphasis>
Clearly visible in dorsal view, comparatively large, triangular, flat, flush with elytra, impunctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,825,2040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,1834,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Elytra.</emphasis>
1.53–1.63 times longer than wide; 1.53–1.63 times longer than pronotum, sides parallel from base to apical for three-fourths of length and then becoming gradually attenuate, apex acuminate. Base slightly bisinuate. Disc shining, striae and interstriae uniseriate punctate, striae with long setae, interstriae with minute shallow punctures and a row of shorter setae. Declivity rugose, dull, striae and interstriae granulate; striae uniseriate granulate, granules rhomboidal, very closely arranged; interstriae broader than striae, covered with one or two rows of irregular minute granules.
</paragraph>
